<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[269,507,187,214]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="63 - 112" refId="ref368107" refString="Rondani, C. (1848 b) Esame di varie specie d'insetti ditteri brasiliani. Studi Entomologici, 1 (1), 63 - 112, pl. IIIbis." type="journal article" year="1848">Rondani (1848b: 96)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<emphasis box="[633,881,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1848" box="[633,877,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Gonypus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviventris">Gonypus breviventris</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
without specifying either the 
<taxonomicName box="[1228,1314,187,213]" family="Number" pageId="53" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
or the sex of the specimens, but giving a single measurement of length, from material collected in South America by V. Ghiliani and received from G. Mussino. 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, A." box="[659,849,259,286]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="13 - 48" refId="ref348459" refString="Costa, A. (1866) Acquisti fatti durante l'anno 1863. Annuario del Museo Zoologico della Regia Universita di Napoli, 3, 13 - 48." type="journal article" year="1866">Costa (1866: 36)</bibRefCitation>
listed a single MZUN specimen (as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1805" box="[1266,1359,259,285]" genus="Gonipes" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1266,1359,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Gonipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis box="[1377,1408,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">sic</emphasis>
!]) numbered “785”. We also found 
<specimenCount box="[573,709,295,321]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="generic" typeStatus="syntype">one syntype</specimenCount>
in this study. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[982,1218,295,322]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="63 - 112" refId="ref368107" refString="Rondani, C. (1848 b) Esame di varie specie d'insetti ditteri brasiliani. Studi Entomologici, 1 (1), 63 - 112, pl. IIIbis." type="journal article" year="1848">Rondani (1848b: 63)</bibRefCitation>
only gave the type locality as “ 
<collectingCountry box="[329,415,331,357]" name="Brazil" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Brasile</collectingCountry>
”, 
<bibRefCitation author="Papavero, N." box="[436,676,331,357]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" refId="ref362581" refString="Papavero, N. (1973) Essays on the history of Neotropical dipterology, with special reference to collectors (1750 - 1905). Vol. 2. Museu de Zoologia, Universidade de Sao Paolo, Sao Paolo, pp. 217 - 446." type="book" year="1973">Papavero (1973: 343)</bibRefCitation>
gave a more accurate type locality based on a note in 
<bibRefCitation author="Spinola, M." box="[1270,1436,330,357]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="19 - 94" refId="ref374743" refString="Spinola, M. (1853) Compte rendu des hymenopteres inedits provenants du voyage entomologique de M. Ghiliani dans le Para en 1846. Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino, Series 2, 13, 19 - 94." type="journal article" year="1853">Spinola (1853)</bibRefCitation>
that said all specimens collected by Ghiliani in 1846 were collected in Belem, Pará, 
<collectingCountry box="[1142,1214,367,393]" name="Brazil" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
